Ms. Winston is a dedicated scholar-practitioner committed to empowering students,
elevating educators, and driving systemic progress. Beginning her journey as an
elementary teacher and math instructional coach in Birmingham City Schools, her
exceptional instructional prowess earned her the title of Teacher of the Year. As a
Teach for America alum, she has shared her expertise nationwide, served as a Math
Coach for School Transformation, and reviewed standardized test items for the
Smarter Balanced Assessment Consortium. Her innovative spirit led her to author a
skills-based elementary math intervention program and guide the integration of
learning progressions into a nationwide curriculum.
About Our Team
As an Educational Consultant, Ms. Winston provides professional development to teachers, instructional coaches, and
administrators on topics ranging from data-driven instruction to creating academic safety. She has consulted with schools,
districts, and states across the country, delivering instructional coaching and professional development in 13 states. With a
background as a Public Relations Executive and Radio Personality, she brings a unique perspective to her role, bridging the gap
between K-12 and post-secondary opportunities.
Ms. Winston’s passion for educational equity and community engagement inspired her to establish Collective Impact. Through
this organization, she collaborates with schools and youth organizations to enhance their academic and enrichment programs
and provides professional development and instructional support. Her expertise, enthusiasm, and dedication make her a
beacon of hope, inspiring the next generation of education leaders and champions for equity.
